-- Shinsei Rises In Tokyo on Plans to Buy Back $1 Billion Prefered Securities
-- B y   J a m e s   G u n s a l u s
-- 2010-11-11T00:04:42Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-11-11/shinsei-rises-in-tokyo-on-plans-to-buy-back-1-billion-prefered-securities.html
Shinsei Bank Ltd., the Japanese
lender partly owned by J. Christopher Flowers, rose as much as
2.9 percent to 72 yen and traded at 71 yen as of 9:01 a.m. in
Tokyo after the company unveiled plans to buy back $1.1 billion
of preferred securities to boost its capital ratio ahead of
tighter Basel regulations.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
James Gunsalus at 
 jgunsalus@bloomberg.net  